Modern Niagara had issues with the hopper, as they have a logo that’s being identified as an invoice and going into the hopper. We need to find a way of identifying such images and avoid sending them to the hopper. For now our check is:   boolean isTinyImage(File file) {
    try {
      BufferedImage image = isNull(file) ? null : ImageIO.read(file);
      return !isNull(image) && image.getWidth() <= imageFileMinWidth && file.length() <= imageFileMinSize;
    } catch (Throwable e) {
      return false;
    }
  } So we are considering it tiny if it’s width is less than the one in the properties AND the file size is less than the one in the properties. For now we can change this condition to OR, so if any of those conditions isn’t met, we consider it tiny. Attached to this ticket is the logo that they are getting into the hopper.

