As an API user We need to support the insertion of catalog items though JSON payload. https://staging-api.vroozi.com/v1/catalogs/{id/externalId}/items/async?version=2 https://staging-api.vroozi.com/v1/catalogs/name/{name}/items/async?version=2 Acceptance Criteria: Limit the items to 5000 , (AWS payload size limit is 10MB) The size of the payload needs to be adjusted after testing, keeping in view the 10MB hard limit on the API gateway payload size. Perform all the required validations and error report Support the header parameter update-strategy with MERGE and REPLACE options. Catalog will store this information in editOption field. Use the stored value. If this is passed in the header than use the header value as preference. If the catalog stored with other values like NEW or COPY, or OTHER, than use the value from header or default to MERGE. Convert this payload into existing catalog file template that can be processed  async Expose the AsycnRequest object in response that will include the requestId, which can be used to track the progress of this async request. {
  "requestId": "123-2123",
  "status": "Processing",
  "timestamp": "2023-03-15T13:56:04.037+0000"
} We need to expose the status tracking end point. Details of the end point - expose the end point  /catalogs/request-tracking/{requestId} The client should be able to get the status by polling. Expose the end point to download the error report. Details of the error report end point - /{requestId}/report  (Separate ticket for error report need to rework as name in template and API does not match.) Store the request and errors in the async_requests collection with requestId. We can store the payload to a separate collection async_requests_payload In the API description, we need to add the following information V ersion is optional field for identifying the correct catalog for which we want to upsert these items. There could be multiple version of the catalog in different columns. If the version is not provided we will consider the latest catalog version for the update. If you want to update specific version of the catalog, please provide in the optional query parameters which version of the catalog should be updated.  If the provided id/externalId/name does not exist, we give validation error {
